title: Kôkaku Kidôtai
overview: A cyborg policewoman and her partner hunt a mysterious and powerful hacker called the Puppet Master.

title: Batman: Mask of the Phantasm
overview: Batman is wrongly implicated in a series of murders of mob bosses actually done by a new vigilante assassin.

title: Jûbê ninpûchô
overview: A vagabond swordsman is aided by a beautiful ninja girl and a crafty spy in confronting a demonic clan of killers - with a ghost from his past as their leader - who are bent on overthrowing the Tokugawa Shogunate.

title: The Lego Movie
overview: An ordinary LEGO construction worker, thought to be the prophesied as "special", is recruited to join a quest to stop an evil tyrant from gluing the LEGO universe into eternal stasis.

title: Akira
overview: A secret military project endangers Neo-Tokyo when it turns a biker gang member into a rampaging psychic psychopath who can only be stopped by two teenagers and a group of psychics.

title: The Iron Giant
overview: A young boy befriends a giant robot from outer space that a paranoid government agent wants to destroy.

title: Vampire Hunter D: Bloodlust
overview: When a girl is abducted by a vampire, a legendary bounty hunter is hired to bring her back.

title: Big Hero 6
overview: A special bond develops between plus-sized inflatable robot Baymax and prodigy Hiro Hamada, who together team up with a group of friends to form a band of high-tech heroes.

title: Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse
overview: Teen Miles Morales becomes the Spider-Man of his universe, and must join with five spider-powered individuals from other dimensions to stop a threat for all realities.

title: Loving Vincent
overview: In a story depicted in oil painted animation, a young man comes to the last hometown of painter Vincent van Gogh (Robert Gulaczyk) to deliver the troubled artist's final letter and ends up investigating his final days there.

title: Kubo and the Two Strings
overview: A young boy named Kubo must locate a magical suit of armour worn by his late father in order to defeat a vengeful spirit from the past.

title: Shin seiki Evangelion Gekijô-ban: Air/Magokoro wo, kimi ni
overview: Concurrent theatrical ending of the TV series Shin seiki evangerion (1995).

title: The Incredibles
overview: A family of undercover superheroes, while trying to live the quiet suburban life, are forced into action to save the world.
stars: ['Craig T. Nelson', 'Samuel L. Jackson', 'Holly Hunter', 'Jason Lee']

title: How to Train Your Dragon 2
overview: When Hiccup and Toothless discover an ice cave that is home to hundreds of new wild dragons and the mysterious Dragon Rider, the two friends find themselves at the center of a battle to protect the peace.

title: Pâfekuto burû
overview: A pop singer gives up her career to become an actress, but she slowly goes insane when she starts being stalked by an obsessed fan and what seems to be a ghost of her past.

title: Despicable Me
overview: When a criminal mastermind uses a trio of orphan girls as pawns for a grand scheme, he finds their love is profoundly changing him for the better.

title: Mononoke-hime
overview: On a journey to find the cure for a Tatarigami's curse, Ashitaka finds himself in the middle of a war between the forest gods and Tatara, a mining colony. In this quest he also meets San, the Mononoke Hime.

title: Rupan sansei: Kariosutoro no shiro
overview: A dashing thief, his gang of desperadoes and an intrepid policeman struggle to free a princess from an evil count's clutches, and learn the hidden secret to a fabulous treasure that she holds part of a key to.

title: Hauru no ugoku shiro
overview: When an unconfident young woman is cursed with an old body by a spiteful witch, her only chance of breaking the spell lies with a self-indulgent yet insecure young wizard and his companions in his legged, walking castle.

title: Udta Punjab
overview: A story that revolves around drug abuse in the affluent north Indian State of Punjab and how the youth there have succumbed to it en-masse resulting in a socio-economic decline.
